<h2 id="details-about-mathjax-lable-and-cite-equations">Details about MathJax (Lable and Cite Equations)</h2>

<p>During the writing of thermodynamics study notes, I came up with the need to label a bunch of equations and cite them in derivations. And after some strugle, I found a way to lable and cite equations.</p>

<p>Below is a simple example, below is a equation, with auto-generated equation-number:</p>

<p>\begin{align}
  c_P - c_V = \frac{\alpha^2 TV}{\kappa_T N}
  \tag{2.16}
  \label{eq-example}
\end{align}</p>

<p>And we can cite \eqref{eq-example} in lines. If this is what you need too, you can continue reading.</p>

<p>With the default configuration of Huxâ€™s blog, we can use the following ways to write equations:</p>

<p>Write equation in-line equation like <code class="highlighter-rouge">$x^2+y^2=R^2$</code> will shows $x^2+y^2=R^2$.</p>

<h2 id="hide-posts-at-homepage">Hide posts at homepage</h2>

<p>Using <code class="highlighter-rouge">hidden: true</code> at post head can hide perticular post at homepage, but itâ€™s still visible at archive, and can be reached through link from neighboring posts.</p>

<p>Using <code class="highlighter-rouge">published: false</code> will totally exclude it from website.</p>

