<h2 id="enable-catalog">Enable Catalog</h2>

<p>Itâ€™s already embaded in Huxâ€™s blog. (<del>But Iâ€™ve finding it for long time Orzâ€¦</del>)</p>

<p>Just adding <code class="highlighter-rouge">catalog: true</code> can enable catalog. It is written in <code class="highlighter-rouge">post.html</code>.</p>

<p>Catalog style: floats at the right of the page.</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>The 1,2,3 heading has the same style, 4,5,6 has the same style.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>However, when the catalog is too long, a scroll bar will appear, which is not beautiful.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>By the way, the method of adding in-post link is using <code class="highlighter-rouge">[Enable Catalog](#enable-catalog)</code> which looks as <a href="#enable-catalog">Enable Catalog</a>.</p>

<h2 id="insert-catalog"><del>Insert catalog</del></h2>

<p>Solved in <a href="#enable-catalog">#Enable Catalog</a>. No need to read this part.</p>

<p>In jekyll, simply write the following line where you want to display the catalog:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="rouge-gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
2
3
4
5
</pre></td><td class="rouge-code"><pre>## Catalog
{:.no_toc} &lt;!--I dont want it itself appears--&gt;

*  
{:toc}
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></div></div>

<p>Reference: <a href="http://www.zhengjiachao.com/topics/github.io/add-outline-on-jekyll-post.html">ç»™JEKYLLçš„æ–‡ç« æ·»åŠ ç›®å½•</a></p>

<h2 id="how-to-write-math-using-latex-grammar-mathjax">How to write math using Latex grammar (mathjax)</h2>

<p>It is already embaded in Huxâ€™s blog.</p>

<p>Add <code class="highlighter-rouge">mathjax: true</code> to enable it.</p>

<p>Note that this effect is different from <code class="highlighter-rouge">## Atom plugin (irrelavent)</code>. That one aims to write math directly in atom, and read, has nothing to do with blog.</p>

<p>Using the following line</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="rouge-gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
</pre></td><td class="rouge-code"><pre>$$ S = \int_{a}^b f(x) \mathrm{d}x = F(b) - F(a) $$
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></div></div>
<p>to show</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">S = \int_{a}^b f(x) \mathrm{d}x = F(b) - F(a)</script>

<p><a href="https://mikelyou.com/2016/05/19/test-math/">temp-post-test-math</a></p>

