<h2 id="customized-excerpts">Customized excerpts</h2>

<p>The excerpts (or abstract) will appear at the list of posts, and by default it is copied from the first some number of words of the post.</p>

<p>Here are two ways to customize the excerpts.</p>

<p><strong>One way is using <code class="highlighter-rouge">excerpt</code> variable.</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Adding the line <code class="highlighter-rouge">excerpt_separator:  '&lt;!-- more --&gt;'</code> in <code class="highlighter-rouge">_config.yml</code>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Go to <code class="highlighter-rouge">index.html</code>, <!--  -->change <code class="highlighter-rouge">{{ post.content }}</code> to <code class="highlighter-rouge">{{ post.excerpt }}</code>. <!--  --></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Then we can do by adding <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;!-- more --&gt;</code> in our postsï¼Œand the auto-copied excerpts will stop there.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<p><strong>The second way is write it directly in post head.</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>We can use <code class="highlighter-rouge">excerpt: Write your excerpt here.</code> at post head directly.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And this will disable auto-generated excerpts.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<p>Reference:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://blog.coderzh.com/2015/08/15/JekyllReadMore/">ä½¿ç”¨Jekyllå®˜æ–¹çš„ReadMoreæ‘˜è¦åŠŸèƒ½</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://moonagic.com/configure-the-jekyll-article-list-summary/">Jekyllæ–‡ç« åˆ—è¡¨æ‘˜è¦è®¾ç½®</a></li>
</ul>

